          <msContents class="lemmatic">
            <summary>This manuscript contains commentary on the book of Aphorisms
                            attributed to <persName type="standard" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/287984736" key="n 80119944 ">Hippocrates</persName>. </summary>
            <msItem>
              <author>
                <name type="unknown" subtype="aut" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/309631400">
                  <persName xml:lang="eng">ʿAli bin Ṭāhir al-Ṭabīb
                                        al-Sinǧārī</persName>
                  <persName xml:lang="ara">علي بن طاهر الطبيب السنجاري</persName>
                </name>
              </author>
              <title xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">Kitāb Taysīr al-Wuṣūl ʾilā
                                tafsīr al-fuṣūl li-ʾAbuqrāṭ</title>
              <title xml:lang="ara">كتاب تيسير الوصول إلى تفسير الفصول لأبقراط</title>
              <title xml:lang="eng" type="desc">Making It Easy to Arrive at an
                                Explanation of Hippocrates’ ‘Aphorisms’ </title>
              <note>This is a lemmatically arranged commentary. The introduction
                                begins on <locus>f. 5b</locus>; the beginning of each Book is as
                                follows: Bk 1: 6a; Bk 2: 13b; Bk 3: 25b; Bk 4 34a; Bk 5: 49b; Bk 6:
                                61b; Bk 7: 69b.</note>
              <respStmt>
